---
/**
 * rest-api/0002 · Figure 5 — "pick the right code — four forks".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0002-http-methods-and-status-codes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Decision mini-map for picking between commonly confused status codes"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">PICK THE RIGHT CODE — FOUR FORKS</text
            >
            <!-- Fork A: 201 vs 200 vs 204 -->
            <rect x="14" y="30" width="280" height="98" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text x="28" y="49" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >Created something new?</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="68" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e">→ 201 + Location (new resource)</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="85" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >→ 200 if returning a body, no new URI</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="102" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >→ 204 success, nothing to send back</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="119" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >typical 204: DELETE / PUT with no body</text
            >
            <!-- Fork B: 400 vs 422 -->
            <rect x="306" y="30" width="280" height="98" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
            <text x="320" y="49" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
                >Bad request — how bad?</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="68" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ 400 syntactically broken / unparseable</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="85" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ 422 parses fine, fails validation</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="105" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >"well-formed JSON, business rule fails"</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="119" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">= 422 Unprocessable Content</text>
            <!-- Fork C: 401 vs 403 -->
            <rect x="14" y="138" width="280" height="98" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="28" y="157" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >Auth problem — which?</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="176" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >→ 401 "we don't know who you are"</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="190" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >authentication — credentials missing/bad</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="209" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a">→ 403 "we know you, you can't"</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="223" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >authorization — identity is fine, no access</text
            >
            <!-- Fork D: 404 vs 410 -->
            <rect x="306" y="138" width="280" height="98" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text x="320" y="157" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Not here — for now or forever?</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="176" font-size="9.5" fill="#2c2a26"
                >→ 404 absent, or hiding existence</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="190" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >404 over 403 avoids leaking it exists</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="209" font-size="9.5" fill="#2c2a26"
                >→ 410 Gone — permanently removed</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="223" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">tells clients to stop asking</text>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The gotcha checklist: 201 needs <code>Location</code> · 401 vs 403 is authn vs authz · 404 hides
        existence on purpose · 307/308 preserve the method · PATCH idempotency depends on the patch ·
        never tunnel errors through a 200.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
